"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(*)\nFROM Examination\nWHERE Thrombosis = 2\n  AND ANA = 'S'\n  AND `aCL IgM` > (SELECT AVG(`aCL IgM`) * 1.2 FROM Examination);\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of patients in the `Examination` table who have a thrombosis level of 2, an ANA pattern of 'S', and an anti-Cardiolipin antibody (IgM) level that is 20% higher than the average."